    "narrative": "The Austin Waves head into today\u2019s slate with **Kyle Tucker** (83.37) as our clear offensive anchor. Facing Lorenzen in a hitter-friendly environment, **Tucker** benefits from a massive 14% park boost and favorable platoon dynamics, making him an elite start. **Miguel Vargas** (66.77) also presents an intriguing high-floor play; while his base projection is modest, the combination of a favorable park, a soft matchup against Springs, and his ability to exploit the pitcher's slow delivery makes him a prime candidate for a stolen base\u2014a critical requirement given our focus on the scarcest 5x5 category. **Andy Pages** (67.38) and **Marcell Ozuna** (63.70) are also locked in as strong plays, with **Ozuna** gaining a late-breaking 5% boost due to wind conditions favoring hitters against McClanahan.\n\nConversely, we are exercising caution with **Gunnar Henderson** (53.28) and **Jackson Merrill** (54.06). While **Henderson** remains a fixture, his platoon disadvantage against Cantillo significantly suppresses his efficiency score compared to his typical ceiling. **Merrill** faces a similar challenge; despite his talent, he is running into a buzzsaw in Urena (2.35 xERA), which heavily weighs down his outlook despite an otherwise solid batting order slot. Our toughest decision involved the bench, where **Heliot Ramos** (52.42) was the final cut. While **Ramos** was considered to provide depth, his projected efficiency fell just short of our starters, particularly against the specific platoon splits presented by the day's pitching staff. \n\nWe are monitoring the status of **Liam Hicks** (41.16) closely, as he remains the most volatile spot in our lineup. His score is bolstered by a favorable platoon edge, but the SP skill of Misiorowski introduces risk that could force a pinch-hit situation later in the game. We are also keeping **Nolan Schanuel**, **Coby Mayo**, and **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** on high alert; should any late-inning lineup changes occur or weather patterns shift, these bench assets are positioned to bridge the gap if our starting core underperforms against their respective targets.",
